Six-time Nyanza region secondary schools&rsquo; girls&rsquo; hockey queens, Sinyolo are gearing up for the seventh title as the regional games get underway tomorrow at Cardinal Otunga High School, Mosocho.Sinyolo coach Alloys Owino said: &ldquo;We still have a very good team and we are ready to defend the title.&rdquo;He said they have no place for complacency despite being the national and East Africa champions. He admitted they have been pitted in a tough pool and face stiff challenge from their opponents.Sinyolo are up against Dede, Nyamira and Nyabururu in Pool &lsquo;B&rsquo; while Kisumu Girls have an easy task against Ambassador Pamela Mboya and Kereri. Boys&rsquo; hockey defending champions Maseno School coach Frank Odayo is also confident of retaining the title but has warned it is not going to be easy. &ldquo;Some schools like St. Mary&rsquo;s Yala, Kanyawanga and Kisii School have good teams which have matured. We don&rsquo;t expect an easy tournament but the boys are ready despite some challenges here and there,&rdquo; said Odayo.Maseno School will play St. Mary&rsquo;s Yala, Kiabonyoru and Kisii School in Pool &lsquo;A&rsquo; while Pool &lsquo;B&rsquo; has Kisumu Day, Kanyawanga, Homa Bay and Nyabigena. In rugby, Maseno are in Pool &lsquo;A&rsquo; alongside Homa Bay High, Nyabigena and Rapogi while Pool &lsquo;B&rsquo; boosts hosts Cardinal Otunga, St. Mary&rsquo;s Yala, Nyambaria High and ThurdubuoroI (Kisumu). In the girls&rsquo; basketball, holders Bar Chando was handed a tough draw in Pool &lsquo;B&rsquo; against Itierio, St. Mary&rsquo;s Mabera and Kisumu whereas pool &lsquo;A&rsquo; has Ekenyoro, Asumbi, Nyamira and Nyabururu. Defending boys&rsquo; basketball champions Kisum have been drawn in Pool &lsquo;A&rsquo; against Kisii School, Agoro Sare and St. Pius Uriri while Pool &lsquo;B&rsquo; has former champions Maseno School, Cardinal Otunga, Ambira and Nyamira&rsquo;s Ekenyoro. The event will also feature cross county, decathlon and heptathlon.